Mandrax tablets, approximately worth R36 000, were found hidden in a taxi on Friday (23/03).Photo: Supplied Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories In an effort to fight crime and eradicate the dealing and abuse of drugs in the community, the police in Prieska confiscated Mandrax tablets with an estimated street value of R36 000 on Friday night (23/03). No arrests have yet been made in connection with the findings, as no one claimed the backpack that contained the drugs. one has yet been arrested in connection with the findings as no one could claim the back-pack that contained it.The police received a tip-off about a taxi, travelling from Kimberley to Prieska, which was appa­rently transporting drugs. According to Lt Col Di­makatso Mooi, the police reacted swiftly and intercepted the identified taxi at approximately 21:45 on Friday. “Upon searching the taxi, 450 Mandrax tablets were found wrapped in a bath towel,” Mooi said. “It is alleged that no one in the taxi had any know­ledge of the drugs or the backpack, and an enquiry was opened.” The community is applauded for working toge­ther with the police and is encouraged to continue reporting any criminal activities to their nearest police station on the Crime Stop line 08600-10111. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  